    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="279"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3187: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 16, 1919—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 23, 7 p.m. For President: American Commissioners cable that they
                    appreciate your attitude toward them and will be glad to render any proper
                    assistance at Conference.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Worley</persName> delayed with details of loan and correspondence.
                    Suggests that <persName>King</persName> and <persName>Dunbar</persName> meet him
                    Hotel Crillon, Paris. American commissioners have been asked to assist in
                    finding temporary or permanent lodging and one office room.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Worley</persName> is cabling <persName>Walker</persName>
                    <note n="6" xml:id="d279fn6">
                        <persName>Walter F. Walker</persName>, Secretary of the Treasury of
                        Liberia.</note> $2,000.</p>
                <p>Office supplies being shipped.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
